04/09/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- President Bamir Topi met on Monday (September 3rd) with representatives of the Independent Trade Union working at the largest mine in the country -- the Bulqiza chrome mine, where four miners have died recently.
Union officials described poor working conditions and asked Topi to intervene on their behalf.
They are demanding better safety conditions and better pay.
(Shekulli, Kohajone, Panorama, Shqip - 04/09/07;
Albanian President web site, Top-Channel - 03/09/07)
